<item>
            <title>[LU-8841] Replace l_wait_info calls that use zeroed info parameters</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8841</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are many cases where l_wait_event is used with an l_wait_info parameter that is completely zeroed.  This is done to wait for new kernel threads to be started (or exit due to a failure).  These cases should be replaced with the native wait_event or wait_event_timeout as appropriate.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An example of the zeroed l_wait_info is in sptlrpc_gc_init:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;struct l_wait_info lwi = { 0 };
...
task = kthread_run(...);
...
l_wait_event(sec_gc_thread.t_ctl_waitq, thread_is_running(&amp;amp;sec_gc_thread), &amp;amp;lwi);

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue was uncovered during the code review at &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/23754/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/23754/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
